        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 3 at 1:59PM CDT by NWS Little Rock AR</headline>
        <description>At 158 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Ozark, moving northeast at 55 mph.

HAZARD...Half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Oak Grove in Johnson County...    Marble Falls...
Valley Springs...                 Yardelle...
Catalpa...                        Western Grove...
Yale...                           Fallsville...
Crossroad...                      Swain...
Gum Springs in Newton County...   Carver...
Oark...                           Hunt...
Nail...                           Wolf Pen Campground...
Arbaugh...                        Point Peter...
Hasty...                          Lurton...
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 1000 PM CDT for
western and north central Arkansas.</instruction>
